Installable tarball extract of the Purple Facebook, with the following fixes:

- Fix ERROR_QUEUE_OVERFLOW
- Build: update.sh: Fix pidgin repository link

In order to build the project, follow the [instructions](https://github.com/dequis/purple-facebook/wiki/Building-on-*NIX) in the upstream wiki.

It's possible to build software packages by using [checkinstall](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CheckInstall): with the program installed, build the project as usual, then run `sudo checkinstall`.

Original description:

> Purple Facebook implements the Facebook Messenger protocol into pidgin,
> finch, and libpurple. While the primary implementation is for purple3,
> this plugin is back-ported for purple2.
>
> This project is not affiliated with Facebook, Inc.
>
> More information: https://github.com/dequis/purple-facebook/wiki
